<title>MEXICO: Mexico's restaurants see recovery in '97.</title>
<headline>Mexico's restaurants see recovery in '97.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1997-02-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mexico's restaurant industry could create up to 80,000 jobs during 1997 as it recovers from the brutal 1994-1995 peso crisis, the Mexican Restaurant Industry Association (Canirac) said on Thursday.</p>
<p>Isaac Finkler, the association's director, told a news conference that the industry had lost 75,000 jobs in 1995 and created some 30,000 jobs last year.</p>
<p>&quot;This year we are in good enough shape to contribute to the jobs recovery nationwide,&quot; Finkler said.</p>
<p>He said the country's restaurants totalled 200,000 and had total sales of 72 billion pesos, &quot;equal to some three percent of GDP.&quot;</p>
<p>((--Veronica Galan, Mexico City newsroom +525 728-9553))</p>
